Text: Can I get pregnant the first time I have sex
Message JSON: {"userId":"37276cb1-4a7a-409c-9b12-dadf2368c470","text":"Can I get pregnant the first time I have sex"}

Text: You can get pregnant any time you have sex. Even if it’s your first time, if it’s his first time, or both of y’all are doing this for the first time together. Doesn’t matter. Use birth control EVERY time you have sex.

Message JSON: {"userId":"37276cb1-4a7a-409c-9b12-dadf2368c470","text":"How do I prevent stds"}

Text: The BEST way to avoid getting an STD is using a condom, EVERY time you have sex. Vaginal, anal, or oral. It’s also a good idea to get tested regularly and have a chat with your guy about it too.

Message JSON: {"userId":"37276cb1-4a7a-409c-9b12-dadf2368c470","text":"What is a good age to have sex"}

Text: Different types of birth control start working at different times  - in general, most of them kick in after about a week. During that first week, you should always use condoms as a back up birth control. The only one that starts working immediately is the copper IUD.

Text: Using other types of birth control with condoms is a great way to protect against both pregnancy and STDs. Lots of birth control methods (like the pill, IUD, implant, patch, ring or the shot) can keep you from getting pregnant, but they don't protect against STDs.

Text: What is the best type of birth control
Message JSON: {"userId":"37276cb1-4a7a-409c-9b12-dadf2368c470","text":"What is the best type of birth control "}

Text: Choosing the best birth control is a really personal decision. There are 18 different types to choose from and they each work differently. You have to use a condom every time you have sex, take the pill daily, get a new patch every week, change the ring every month, and the IUD or implant can last for years.

Text: Where do I go to get on birth control
Message JSON: {"userId":"37276cb1-4a7a-409c-9b12-dadf2368c470","text":"Where do I go to get on birth control "}

Text: Birth control is super easy to get. I know it sounds like a lot of work but seriously, it’s not that bad. There was a time when you could ONLY get it through your doctor but these days, you can get lots of different kinds online. Yes girl, online! Condoms, the pill, patch, ring, and even the morning after pill are available. You just need to answer a few questions and maybe meet with a doctor online and that’s it! Check out these websites to find online birth control: Prjkt Ruby, The Pill Club, Nurx, and Vagisil.

Text: You can get pregnant any time you have sex. This means at any time during the month, even on your period. Sperm can survive up to 5 DAYS in a woman’s body so even towards the end of your period, you’re risking pregnancy.
